name: 2014 Wall Calendar
description:
The images featured in the 2014 calendar are from my new series: Vintage Vehicles.  Though I don't know much about the vehicles themselves, I am in love with their shapes and forms.  There is a beautiful quality to their current state - a story of their past life worn proudly in their faded paint and patches of rust.  I tracked down and photographed these dilapidated beauties, in all their rusty glory, primarily within a 50-mile radius of my home in Napa, CA.  Each month includes the location where I found the featured vehicle.

Dimensions: 11" x 17"

Printed on smooth matte paper so you can make notes easily in either pencil or pen.

Calendars are loose-leaf (unbound), but held together with a string.  Hang individual pages to view several months at once or all together from the string to save space.

Images & Design ©2013 Jessica Rogers Photography, All Rights Reserved

name: Oak Pods 1
description:
Matted Print of "Oak Pods 1"

Here's a little science lesson for the day:  Oak pods (more commonly known as Oak galls) are formed when the Gall wasp lays it's eggs on the Oak tree.  The tree, in a defensive reaction, forms these "pods" around the area.  In the end, the tree isn't harmed and the pods provide a safe place for the baby wasps to grow up.  When they are old enough, they bore a hold in the pod and fly away.  Fortunately for me, I photographed these pods after they had been emptied!
